      { heading: "Ahrefs Backlink Checker: The Best Free Option", body: "Ahrefs offers the most generous free backlink checker available. Enter any domain to see its top one hundred backlinks, domain rating, URL rating, referring domains, and the most linked-to pages. The free tool shows anchor text distribution, follow versus nofollow ratio, and link type breakdowns. You also get a limited view of the site organic traffic and keyword rankings. While the data is not as comprehensive as the paid version, which would show all backlinks, the free version provides sufficient data for a meaningful analysis of most sites. For competitive research, enter competitor domains to understand their link-building strategies." },
      { heading: "Moz Link Explorer for Domain Authority Analysis", body: "Moz Link Explorer provides free link data including domain authority, page authority, spam score, and linking root domains. The free tier allows a limited number of queries per month but provides actionable insights. Moz spam score metric is particularly valuable for identifying potentially toxic backlinks that could harm your rankings. The tool also shows anchor text distribution and top pages by links. Moz Link Explorer integrates with the MozBar browser extension, allowing you to check metrics while browsing any page. The domain authority metric is widely used as an industry benchmark for comparing site authority across competitors." },
      { heading: "Monitor Backlinks for New and Lost Links", body: "Monitor Backlinks offers a unique free feature: it tracks new and lost backlinks over time, sending email notifications when your link profile changes. Setting up a free account gives you a limited dashboard showing your top backlinks, referring domains, and anchor text distribution. The timeline view is particularly useful for understanding when links were acquired or lost, helping you correlate link changes with ranking fluctuations. The free tier is limited in the number of domains you can track and the frequency of updates, but it provides more temporal data than one-time checkers like Ahrefs or Moz free versions." },
      { heading: "OpenLinkProfiler for Comprehensive Backlink Data", body: "OpenLinkProfiler is a completely free tool with no daily query limits. It provides backlink data including link source, anchor text, link type, and the first seen and last seen dates. The tool excels at finding low-quality or spammy links because it indexes a broad range of web pages. You can export the full list of backlinks to CSV for offline analysis. While the user interface is less polished than Ahrefs or Moz, the depth of data and lack of restrictions make it invaluable for link audits. The tool also provides a toxic score that helps identify links worth disavowing." },
      { heading: "Using Backlink Checkers for Competitive Intelligence", body: "Free backlink checkers are powerful competitive intelligence tools when used strategically. Enter up to five competitor domains and compare their backlink profiles to identify patterns. Look for referring domains that link to multiple competitors but not to you, as these represent link-building opportunities. Analyze the anchor text distribution of competitors to understand their keyword focus. Identify the content types that attract the most backlinks for competitors, such as original research, infographics, or comprehensive guides. Review competitors newest backlinks to discover their active link-building tactics. Use these insights to prioritize your own link-building efforts toward proven strategies." }
